{"TopicId":139820,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mesklin-style planet","CreatedByName":"MedwedianPresident","CreatedById":12212,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T14:11:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MedwedianPresident","CreatedById":12212,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T14:11:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022McKenna_--_Mesklin_from_Toorey_(small).j\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.munchkinpress.com/cpg149/albums/userpics/10016/McKenna_--_Mesklin_from_Toorey_(small).jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that a \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesklin\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMesklin\u003C/a\u003E-style planet (from Mission of Gravity by Hal Clement) mod would be a good addition to KSP. It should be a large gaseous or rocky planet which rotates very quickly, meaning that it a.) is extremely oblate and b.) the gravity on the equator is much lower (0.5-2 g) than on the poles (5-10 g or more).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T20:19:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know, I\u0027d rather not introduce complete science fiction. \u00A0There are plenty\u00A0of unique, \u00A0real planets to use as inspiration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T20:29:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222583575\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139820\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463343571\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know, I\u0027d rather not introduce complete science fiction. \u00A0There are plenty\u00A0of unique, \u00A0real planets to use as inspiration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaumea then ? Though a bit small to have 10g at the poles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T20:41:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter seeing Sarnus in OPM, I\u0027d like a Saturn/Uranus\u00A0analog.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-15T20:44:45Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2016 08:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}